This is the Recollection Room. You can view event scenes and
post-clear bonuses here.

Additionally, by checking the location of each event scene,
the conditions for unlocking the corresponding event will be
displayed.

Here you can view hints about the progression and outcomes
of the story. Please be aware that this may include
spoilers.
How to Proceed to the Final Battle

Generally, CGs can only be collected during the
corresponding match period, with some exceptions. (For
example, CGs from the first match period cannot be collected
after the second match begins.)

Additionally, the event scene records are saved even after
starting a separate game, so you can save, view different
routes, and then reload your data to continue.
各種エンド条件について

The following contains spoilers, so if you're concerned,
please press the "ctrl key" to skip.

"BAD END 1" is reached if you cannot pay Yuia's life
extension fee at the management office.

"BAD END 2" is reached by progressing the story without
defeating the lord of the ruins that can be entered during
the fourth battle, leading to this end midway through the
fifth battle.

"Hojiko END" is reached if you face defeat against any
opponent in the training matches and then head towards
Hojiko after starting the fifth battle.

"Fubii END" is reached if you face defeat against any
opponent in the training matches and then head towards Fubii
after starting the fifth battle.

"Rozaro END" is reached if you face defeat against any
opponent in the training matches and then head towards
Rozaro after starting the fifth battle.

"Hebeta END" is reached if you face defeat against any
opponent in the training matches and then head towards
Rozaro after starting the fifth battle.

"Normal END" is reached if you face defeat against any
opponent in the training matches and then start the fifth
battle.

"Normal END" is also reached by making a choice after the
fifth battle to head towards either Irime's husband or
Zuuteruka, and then facing the final battle.

"True END" is achieved by winning against all opponents in
the training matches and using "Weakness Transdermal Poison"
to win against Irime.

During the fifth battle, enter the ruins with Rozaro and
input the code to disarm the trap that was set. The code has
been mentioned by someone by the fourth battle.

In the training matches, if you are defeated by any opponent
even once, you will not be able to proceed to the final
battle.

As an exception, after the fifth battle, choosing to "head
to Irime's house" also allows you to proceed to the final
battle, but this will confirm a Normal END.
遺跡と物語進行について

At the lake ruins on the outskirts of town, you can enhance
Segi and acquire items, but it's possible to progress
through the story without ever setting foot there.

However, if you have not traversed the ruins that become
accessible by the fourth match, you will not be able to
progress further in the story and a bad end will be
confirmed, so please be careful.
人物出現場所と物語の進行

Key characters in the story generally appear in
predetermined locations. For example: Rozaro (tavern), Irime
(Irime's house), etc.

Therefore, if nothing more happens when you go to a
designated place, consider returning home to sleep and let
time pass, which may advance the story.
How to progress through the ruins in the 4th match
リュダ行軍記録について

"Lyuda Military Records 1-6" can generally be purchased
within the management office by eliminating the lord of
ruins that can be entered during each match.

Therefore, if you proceed to the next match without entering
the ruins, you will also be unable to obtain the military
records, so please be careful.

However, if you have eliminated the lord of the ruins during
a previous match, you can purchase and view them in later
chapters.
第4試合時の遺跡の進み方

There are correct and incorrect routes in the ruins that
become accessible by the fourth match. If it's the correct
route after passing through a door and moving forward, a
certain marker will be placed there.
シーン回収について（微ネタバレ）

Here we note the best timing for saving & loading to
efficiently collect scenes. This includes minor spoilers, so
if you're concerned, please skip this hint.

Win all battles up to the third... Save before "preparations
for celebration" two days before the fourth battle...
Progress through the story and repeat choices then save &
load.

Win the fourth battle using the skill "Transdermal
Poison"... Save right before fighting in the fifth battle...
Proceed with the story after either winning or losing.

After reaching any END, reload just before the fifth
battle... Repeat this process and view each END.

Reload just before the fifth battle again and face a
different outcome than before... Then continue with the
story.

This is the recollection room after clearing the game.

If you wish to start the game again, please return to the
title and select New Game.

Please note that the events recorded in this recollection
room can still be viewed after starting a New Game.

\C[10][Caution] After restarting a New Game, if you exit the
recollection room of this cleared data, the game data may
malfunction and you will not be able to re-enter.

\C[10][Caution] Additionally, playing with different data stored
in the same folder as this cleared data may result in being
unable to exit the recollection room after entering.

\C[10][Caution] To avoid this situation, it is strongly
recommended to store this cleared data separately.

\C[10][Caution] By storing it separately, even if you play the
game with other data and view new events, the history will
be preserved in this recollection room.

\C[10][Caution] There is no impact on re-entry and progress in a
New Game, but please be careful. We apologize for any
inconvenience.\C[0]
